WEBVTT

00:00:00.962 --> 00:00:04.125
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:00:04.686 --> 00:00:18.380
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:00:19.121 --> 00:00:26.649
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:00:26.709 --> 00:00:27.890
Today,

00:00:27.970 --> 00:00:36.001
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:00:40.768 --> 00:00:41.369
Peace be with you.

00:00:41.409 --> 00:00:48.559
We come to this second Sunday of Lent and the readings are always rich during Lent because we're getting back to spiritual basics.

00:00:48.599 --> 00:00:53.225
The church wants us to really reflect on some of these elemental truths in the spiritual life.

00:00:53.766 --> 00:00:54.787
And this is a good example.

00:00:55.749 --> 00:00:56.850
I want to start with

00:00:56.994 --> 00:01:00.017
The first reading, which is from the book of Genesis, and it's talking about Abraham.

00:01:00.597 --> 00:01:05.843
And everybody, whatever the Bible talks about Abraham, our ears should perk up.

00:01:05.863 --> 00:01:09.486
Our eyes should get more focused because he's our father in faith.

00:01:10.107 --> 00:01:15.632
He's the one through whom the rescue operation commences.

00:01:18.094 --> 00:01:22.699
Whatever we have of faith in a way is just imitating what Abraham had.

00:01:22.739 --> 00:01:24.521
So we pay special attention.

00:01:25.021 --> 00:01:26.002
We'll listen now to

00:01:26.786 --> 00:01:27.487
