00:01:28.148 --> 00:01:40.244
The Lord said to Abram, that's what they call him here before the name was changed, go forth from the land of your kinsfolk and from your father's house to a land that I will show you.

00:01:40.845 --> 00:01:44.049
And then I'll make you a great nation, right?

00:01:44.069 --> 00:01:47.133
And all the communities of the earth shall find their blessing in you.

00:01:48.175 --> 00:01:52.881
Well, can I suggest to you, this is at the heart of the spiritual life.

00:01:52.961 --> 00:01:53.402
Now why?

00:01:54.323 --> 00:01:56.626
Well, as Augustine said, and I often quote him here,

00:01:57.026 --> 00:02:03.798
Sin is the state of being curvatus in sei, which means caved in upon oneself.

00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:11.752
Sin is always like a black hole that draws everything, including my own powers, kind of inward.

00:02:13.315 --> 00:02:19.506
